Here’s to soaring high and embracing the fear, for it is in the leap that we truly learn to fly!

pov : It’s summer movie night

Every step was a lesson, every follower a blessing. Gratful for this journey and all the support 🔥 Get it know me! ⬇️

I started making content around 8 years ago. My sister got me into it when she introduced me to an app called Musically. I started creating for about 4 months and grew quite a bit to 100,000 but i wasn’t spending time studying and focusing to much on content and my dad was angry and pushed me to quit, so I did. 

A couple years later I watched all the creators that didn’t quit create full creators out of social media and I realized not lissening to my heart lost me a head start.

When musically turned into Tiktok, I decided I had to learn from this and I wouldn’t ever skip a day of posting.

I posted videos 5-10 times a day for 3 years straight and became one of the 20 most followers tiktokers of 2021 and had the 11th most accumulated views on the app of the whole year.

I then decide to do it full time and I quit law school and became a full time creator. It was one of the scariest decisions of my life, but i am beyond grateful I did.

My biggest goal this year is to focus on building my community because i’m sure a lot of you don’t know who I am, but I really hope to change that and make an impact!
